body:
on second pass of jane park's review, I think it is sort of right. the implementation is correct here in the sense that name and category are are being passed to the correct args for segment. However, they're named wrong. I think we want this signature instead:
```
export const trackPageView = (
 category: string,
 options?: {
 name?: string;
 properties?: Record<string, unknown>;
 }
)
```

and then pass to segment like this
`window.analytics?.page(category, options?.name, options?.properties);`

although syntactically I think using a destructured object for the signature would be best:
```
export const trackPageView = (
{category, name, properties}
: {category: string,
 name?: string;
 properties?: Record<string, unknown>;
 }
)
```

