body:
can we have this managed with an orm hook instead?

gpt says it would look something like this in mikro orm
```
@BeforeUpdate()
setUpdatedAtIfRelevant(args: EventArgs<Workspace>) {
 const changed = args.changeSet?.diff ?? args.changeSet?.payload ?? {};
 if ('billingPlanName' in changed) {
 this.billingPlanUpdatedAt = new Date();
 }
}
```

this way we ensure if another functions ends up modifying it the time stamp is still correct.

would actually prefer a db level trigger here so that any direct modifications through raw sql touch the timestamp, but it appears we don't really use db triggers so orm hook feels appropriate.

